Constructor Detail

Unit

public Unit(int SN,
            double[][] readings,
            double[][] resistance)
Constructor. All necessary calculations completed on construction as called by this.initialize().

Parameters:
SN - Serial Number of Unit
readings - Voltage output from units. readings[i][j] corresponds to the jth pressure tested at the ith temperature
resistance - Input and output resistance. resistance[0][j] corresponds to the input resistance at the jth temperature; resistance[1][j] corresponds to the output resistance at the jth temperature
Method Detail

initialize

private void initialize()
Calculates necessary characteristics from this.readings array. This includes FSO, TCRs, Null Shifts, Least-Squares Linearity, Hysteresis, Null Set, and NFSO Set as well as some helpful multipliers.

calcTCRS

private void calcTCRS()
The Cold-Hot, Cold-Room, Room-Hot TCRs are calculated. (Resistance[warmer temp] - Resistance[colder temp]) / (warmerTemp - colderTemp) * (100 / RTinputR) * 100 UNITS: (%/100F)

calcNullShift

private void calcNullShift()
The Cold-Hot, Cold-Room, Room-Hot Null Shifts are calculated. (ouputV[warmer temp] - outputV[colder temp]) / (warmerTemp - colderTemp) * (100 / FSO[RT]) * 100 UNITS: (%/100F)

calcMisc

private void calcMisc()
Calls for calculation of remaining characteristics: Linearity, Hysteresis, Null Set, NFSO Set

calcLinearity

private void calcLinearity()
Least-squares best fit line calculated. this.lin = (max residual from BFL) / FSO * 100 UNITS: %FSO

calcHysteresis

private void calcHysteresis()
Max Hysteresis calculated. Using output data from first RT reading, max hysteresis is calculated: maxDifference / FSO * 100 UNITS: %FSO

calcNullSet

private void calcNullSet()
Calculates difference between 0psi readings at RT readings. UNITS: mV

calcNFSOSet

private void calcNFSOSet()
Calculates difference in Normalized FSO between RT readings. UNITS: mV
